                            <comment id="14721135" author="aivanov" created="Tue, 12 Nov 2024 05:22:04 -0800"  >The test has now been updated. Yet I&amp;#39;ll still add some analysis I did.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I looked at the failures of the test in the CI and found that the test timed out. The screenshot showed a dialog with the &#8220;Test&#8221; title in the top left corner of the screen.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
According to the stack traces (attached as ScaledTransform.java-stacktrace.txt), the main thread called `dialog.setVisible(true)` but paint was never called.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I noticed that there are 210 identical device configurations on my Ubuntu 22.04 VM. On my Windows laptop, there&amp;#39;s one device configuration for each device / monitor.</comment>
