                            <comment id="14458933" author="prr" created="Tue, 16 Nov 2021 14:10:51 -0800"  >This was run on an 800x600 screen config which isn&amp;#39;t something we use/see any more.&lt;br/&gt;
Generally 1920x1080 is the standard screen config for headful testing.&lt;br/&gt;
Could we be unable to support the 2x scale on such a small display in some scenario ?&lt;br/&gt;
The test looks a bit flaky to me. The main thread is used but I guess the paint() method is called on another thread.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;passed&amp;quot; is volatile but I don&amp;#39;t see how the code guarantees to wait for the dialog to have had paint() called.&lt;br/&gt;
Then the test may think it failed since passed is not yet set to true.&lt;br/&gt;
Could be that dialog.dispose() is then called before the dialog setVisible(false) and some how this blocks the hiding ?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
